Deprecated API

  • Deprecated Classes

  • Deprecated Classes 
    Class and Description
    org.thymeleaf.util.EvaluationUtil
    in 3.0.0 for naming homogeneity reasons. Use the equivalent EvaluationUtils class instead. This class will be removed in 3.1.
  • Deprecated Methods 
    Method and Description
    org.thymeleaf.templateresolver.AbstractConfigurableTemplateResolver.computeResourceName(IEngineConfiguration, String, String, String, String, Map<String, String>, Map<String, Object>)
    in 3.0.6. Use AbstractConfigurableTemplateResolver.computeResourceName(IEngineConfiguration, String, String, String, String, boolean, Map, Map) instead. Will be removed in Thymeleaf 3.2.
    org.thymeleaf.util.ObjectUtils.convertToArray(Object)
    since 2.1, you should use the IStandardConversionService implementation corresponding to the dialect you are using or the methods in EvaluationUtils. Will be removed in 3.0.

    since 2.1, you should use the IStandardConversionService implementation corresponding to the dialect you are using or the methods in EvaluationUtils. Will be removed in 3.0.

    since 2.1, you should use the IStandardConversionService implementation corresponding to the dialect you are using or the methods in EvaluationUtils. Will be removed in 3.0.
    org.thymeleaf.standard.expression.FragmentExpression.createExecutedFragmentExpression(IExpressionContext, FragmentExpression, StandardExpressionExecutionContext)
    Deprecated in 3.0.9. Use the version without "expContext" itself, as all FragmentExpressions should be executed in RESTRICTED mode (no request parameter use allowed).
